---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const title = 'Terms · Rekraft Design';
const description = 'The terms under which Rekraft Design takes on bespoke project work.';
const canonical = 'https://rekraft.design/terms';
const lastUpdated = '1 May 2026';
---

<Base title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Nav />
  <main class="legal">
    <div class="frame legal-back-wrap">
      <a href="/" class="legal-back font-mono">&larr; Home</a>
    </div>

    <section class="section legal-hero">
      <div class="frame">
        <header class="legal-head">
          <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
          <h1 class="display-1">Terms.</h1>
          <p class="lead">The basics of how a project with Rekraft Design works, in plain English. The full terms are agreed per project in a signed scope document.</p>
          <p class="legal-meta font-mono">Last updated &middot; {lastUpdated}</p>
        </header>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section legal-body">
      <div class="frame legal-prose">

        <h2>About Rekraft Design</h2>
        <p>Rekraft Design is a small independent design studio based in London, UK. We are sister site to <a href="https://rekraft.agency" target="_blank" rel="noopener">rekraft.agency</a>, which is the productised offer for UK tradespeople. Rekraft Design takes on a small number of bespoke projects each quarter for general clients: brand, websites, and social.</p>

        <h2>What this page is</h2>
        <p>A summary of how a typical engagement works. Every project we take on is governed by a signed scope of work that supersedes anything on this page. If there is a conflict, the signed document wins.</p>

        <h2>How a project starts</h2>
        <p>You write to <a href="mailto:mark@rekraft.design">mark@rekraft.design</a> with what you are trying to build and the timeline you have in mind. We have a discovery conversation. If we are a fit and the calendar lines up, we send a written proposal with scope, deliverables, timing, and price. The project begins once the proposal is signed and the deposit invoice is paid.</p>

        <h2>Payment</h2>
        <p>Standard structure for bespoke work is a deposit on signing, milestones tied to delivery, and a final balance on handover. Invoices are payable within fourteen days. Late payments accrue interest at the statutory rate under the Late Payment of Commercial Debts (Interest) Act 1998.</p>

        <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
        <p>On full payment of all fees, you own the final deliverables. We retain the right to display the finished work in our portfolio and case studies, including on this site, unless the scope document specifies otherwise. The working files, source code, and process artefacts remain ours unless explicitly handed over.</p>

        <h2>Confidentiality</h2>
        <p>We treat anything you share about your business, your customers, and your roadmap as confidential, and we will not share it with third parties except sub-processors we need to deliver the work (covered in the <a href="/privacy">Privacy notice</a>). If you need a separate NDA, we will sign one.</p>

        <h2>Revisions and scope</h2>
        <p>Each project includes a defined number of revision rounds at each milestone, set out in the scope document. Work outside the agreed scope is quoted as a change request before we start it.</p>

        <h2>Termination</h2>
        <p>Either side can end the engagement on written notice. If the project ends mid-flight, fees accrued to that point are due, you keep what you have paid for, and we hand over the relevant files in their current state.</p>

        <h2>Liability</h2>
        <p>Our liability for any single project is capped at the total fees paid by you for that project. We do not exclude or limit liability where the law does not permit us to: death, personal injury, or fraud.</p>

        <h2>Governing law</h2>
        <p>These terms and any signed scope document are governed by the laws of England and Wales. Any disputes go to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of England and Wales.</p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>Questions about these terms or a specific project go to <a href="mailto:mark@rekraft.design">mark@rekraft.design</a>.</p>

        <p class="legal-foot">These terms may be updated from time to time. The date at the top will reflect the latest version. Updates do not affect projects that are already underway, which remain governed by the scope document signed at the start.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Base>

<style>
  .legal-back-wrap { padding-top: clamp(96px, 12vw, 140px); }
  .legal-back {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    color: var(--color-ink-dim);
    font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    transition: color .35s var(--ease-out-expo);
  }
  .legal-back:hover { color: var(--color-ink); }

  .legal-hero { padding-block: clamp(32px, 4vw, 56px) clamp(40px, 5vw, 64px); }
  .legal-head {
    display: grid;
    gap: 16px;
    max-width: 800px;
  }
  .legal-head h1 { color: var(--color-ink); }
  .legal-head .lead { color: var(--color-ink-muted); max-width: 60ch; }
  .legal-meta {
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-ink-dim);
    margin-top: 8px;
  }

  .legal-body {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding-block: clamp(48px, 6vw, 96px);
  }
  .legal-prose {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin-inline: auto;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
    font-size: clamp(16px, 0.5vw + 14px, 18px);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .legal-prose h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    color: var(--color-ink);
    font-size: clamp(24px, 2vw + 12px, 36px);
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-top: clamp(40px, 4vw, 56px);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .legal-prose h2:first-of-type { margin-top: 0; }
  .legal-prose p { margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .legal-prose strong { color: var(--color-ink); font-weight: 600; }
  .legal-prose a {
    color: var(--color-ink);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-cream);
    text-underline-offset: 4px;
    transition: text-decoration-color .25s var(--ease-out-expo);
  }
  .legal-prose a:hover { text-decoration-color: var(--color-ink); }

  .legal-foot {
    margin-top: clamp(40px, 4vw, 64px);
    padding-top: clamp(24px, 3vw, 36px);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--color-ink-dim);
  }
</style>
